<chapter>
  <title>Using SystemImager with Flamethrower for Multicast Installs HOWTO</title>
  
  <section>
    <title>
      Install SystemImager v3.2.x or higher
    </title>
   
	<para>
	</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
      Install the <application>Flamethrower</application> Package and its Dependencies
    </title>
   
	<para>
	</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
      Run getimage, mvimage, or cpimage
    </title>
   
	<para>
      Flamethrower is a stand-alone utility, but SystemImager maintains
      a SystemImager seperate copy (/etc/systemimager/flamethrower.conf)
      of the Flamethrower configuration file 
      (/etc/flamethrower/flamethrower.conf).  Each of these three
      commands (getimage, mvimage, cpimage) will create an appropriate
      entry in /etc/systemimager/flamethrower.conf for the image you
      specify.
	</para>
	<para>
      It is also possible to manually add an entry, if you feel
      compelled to to so.  Take a look at the flamethrower.conf man
      page, or the comments inside the configuration file (image entries
      go at the very bottom of the file).  However, it's much easier to
      just do a &quot;mvimage orig_name tmp_name &amp;&amp; mvimage tmp_name
      orig_name&quot;.
	</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
      Start up your Flamethrower daemon
    </title>
   
	<para>
      Edit /etc/systemimager/flamethrower.conf, and change
      <programlisting>
        START_FLAMETHROWER_DAEMON = no
      </programlisting>
      to
      <programlisting>
        START_FLAMETHROWER_DAEMON = yes
      </programlisting>
	</para>
    <para>
      Then crank it up with a
      <programlisting>
        /etc/init.d/systemimager-server-flamethrowerd restart
      </programlisting>
    </para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
      Tell your autoinstall clients to use Flamethrower
    </title>
   
	<para>
      If you use DHCP, you can add the following to your dhcpd.conf file:
      <programlisting>
        option option-143 "9000";
      </programlisting>
      Then restart your DHCP daemon.  This is usually
      <programlisting>
        /etc/init.d/dhcp restart
      </programlisting>
      or
      <programlisting>
        /etc/init.d/dhcpd restart
      </programlisting>
	</para>
    <para>
      If you use a local.cfg file, you can add the following to that
      file:
      <programlisting>
        FLAMETHROWER_DIRECTORY_PORTBASE=9000
      </programlisting>
    </para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>
      Autoinstall your clients!
    </title>
   
	<para>
      Boot your clients from your favorite autoinstall media (network,
      floppy, CD, or hard drive) and off you go.
	</para>
  </section>

